<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id1246bfc6-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s3314"><num value="3314">§ 3314.</num><heading> Procedures for disposal of records exclusive</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The procedures prescribed by this chapter are exclusive, and records of the United States Government may not be alienated or destroyed except under this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id1246bfc7-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1302">82 Stat. 1302</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
